Uncover the secret life of Agatha Christie, Queen of Crime Explore the globe trotting adventures that inspired 66 thrilling murder mysteries, making Agatha Christie one of the best selling novelists in history This souvenir catalogue follows in the footsteps of the Queen of Crime and examines various aspects of her personal life, her compelling stories and her connections with archaeology Clues to Christie s life and work are found in key artifacts, including her 1937 Remington typewriter, photographs and other personal effects, Mesopotamian and Egyptian antiquities from trips abroad with her archaeologist husband Sir Max Mallowan, as well as items from the famous train featured in one of her most memorable mysteries, Murder on the Orient Express. Best Read [ 
